		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=384524"><span id=Scholar>Teleos</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />293 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.59]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Teleos&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Well, this is situational. Different classes have different capacities. A shaman with bazaar focus gear and a mind buff can kite an ice giant in everfrost at 36, though efficient killing comes later. <br><br>You are not far off killing in Rathe mountains, though you won't want adds if your solo. As a Wizard you have snare which is more than I had as shaman doing hill giants. Of course you can access these mobs with a duo or small group.<br><br>I guess you know about trade skills items... the usual advice... find out whats hot for your server and try and get some.<br><br>As has been said many times, keeping a smart eye out for bazaar specials and reselling for a modest profit is possible (less so with server numbers low I guess).<br><br></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Hack that mob to bits.. get it down to ones and zeros fast!</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
