		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=208497"><span id=Scholar>Valzarius Defender of Justice</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="80" width="80" src="/uf/Valzarius/kwabbit.jpg"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />385 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.37]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Valzarius&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Depending upon how patient you are around the mid 30s there are a couple of options that will allow you to earn cash and get some XP at the same time.<br><br>1) Snow Cougars in Iceclad Ocean - the drop rate on these has been significantly nerfed, so the price of the Cougar Claw earing has increased dramatically (around 250pp on my server).&nbsp;&nbsp;I always thought that this was an underated item, for it gives you STR, AC, and Mana Preservation I. [Note to the cleric - a mana point saved is a mana point earned.  Reducing the amount of mana you consume is  almost as good as having a larger mana pool.   If cash is a problem make friends with a low level magician and have him/her summon you up some goodies]<br><br>2) If you can get a small group together (or even a partner) Najena can be quite entertaining and profitable in the late 20s to early 30s.  You have to be very careful what you pull and be careful of the traps.  The big ticket items here are the magician focus item components that sell very nicely in the Bazaar (frequently for 250pp a crack).  Many magicians are too lazy to get these on their own and will pay top dollar.<br><br>3) Keep an eye out for anything that will make a training rune that can be used to increase your Research skill.  Watch out for research components for popular spells.  Many enchanter spells fall into this category, and the necessary pages are often quite scarce.<br><br>4) When you get high enough look for specific categories of mobs that will drop spells.  Depending upon how rare the drops are you can make a nice profit hording these.  Shardwurms in the Great Divide are a good starting point, and many mobs in Velks and Skyfire fall into this category.<br><br>5) Gornit in the Ocean of Tears is a pushover of a mob and can easily be soloed.  On some occassions he can drop up to 34pp and has a fairly quick respawn time.  Save the giant toes for some can be valuable, along with the fine steal weapons.<br><br></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Kill the wabbit,<br>Kill the wabbit...</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
