		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.07]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=martenp&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Also on FV, with a mid 30's charrie.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>Good suggestions already posted, here's my addendum.<br><br>Farm silks and skins, make leather padding, and set up in bazaar.  Sold out 5 stacks in an hour.  That's if you set up in bazaar.<br><br>As to farming and selling to merchants/vendors, will-o-wisps.  Go lightning bug hunting in the karanas.  (You can also pick up a ton of skins and meat, which will sell well in bazaar.)<br><br>And when you get a little higher, grimlings.  Grimlings drop acrylia and runes that sell well to vendors.  <br><br>I can generally make between 150 and 200pp in an hour or so of farming and selling to vendors.  <br><br>*****<br>Don't discount picking up your &quot;junk loot&quot; either.  All those dumb rusty swords and chunks of meat that sell for silvers can add up.  Of course, the rusty crap is heavy, and you need to sell frequently, but there are plenty of places to farm that have merchants right there.  Freeport comes to mind, there's a gnome right out there in the killing field.  While waiting for the Fabled Fippy to pop in Qeynos, my baby chanter racked up 28PP whacking skellies, bats and snakes and selling to the merchant by the guards.  <br><br>Farming is boring, but necessary, especially if you wish to tradeskill for fun and profit.  <br><br><i><span class="sm">Edited, Thu Mar 24 18:08:53 2005 by martenp</span class="sm"></i></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Mar'ten <br>Level 49 bard AR - Temple Draconis<br>Level 34 bard FV - Mortal Ascension<br>(along with assorted alts) <br></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
