		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=1286"><span id=Encyclopedia>gbaji</span></a><b><span id=Encyclopedia><br>Encyclopedia</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />9757 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.02]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=gbaji&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p><blockquote><b id="fs8">Goalkeeper wrote:</b><hr size="1" /><blockquote><b id="fs8">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />Fv is not the server to make plat on&nbsp;&nbsp;or start there.     <hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>Hah, shows how much you know. FV is EQ's money cow, doll. With almost any item flagged not No Drop, it's yours to milk. <hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>Was going to comment on that as well. Since FV removes the no-drop flag from almost all items, there are a *lot* more really good items available. That means that you can gear up a new character a lot easier on that server then others (a good thing on a server where you only get one character per account!).<br><br>It also means that there's a more vibrant market then on other servers. You wont get as much farming items, but the tradeskill market can be pretty huge. FV also has some code that prevents certain flagged items (I think anything lore or magic?) from dropping from a green con mob. What this means is that you can farm stuff at a low level that higher level folks need for tradeskilling and sell them for good amounts of money. On any other server, you'll find high level characters farming green mobs for stuff they need/want. On FV, the lower level characters can get that stuff and sell it for a tidy profit.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from San Diego, CA</td></tr></table>
